      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 18 article about closing arguments in corruption case against Gerald P Garson, former State Supreme Court justice in Brooklyn, misstated name of his wife, Brooklyn Civil Court Judge Robin Garson</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Wednesday about closing arguments in a corruption case against Gerald P. Garson, a former State Supreme Court justice in Brooklyn, misstated the name of his wife, a Brooklyn Civil Court judge who was in the courtroom. She is Robin Garson, not Rachel.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article on Wednesday about closing arguments in a corruption case against Gerald P. Garson, a former State Supreme Court justice in Brooklyn, misstated the name of his wife, a Brooklyn Civil Court judge who was in the courtroom. She is Robin Garson, not Rachel.</p>
      </block>
